OL,3,CEx-BBC correspondent in Africa says
OL,4,Cfirst reaction to Live Aid was 'real
OL,5,Canger'
OL,7,FAsked how he feels about Live Aid now
OL,8,Fhe said: "I think it was extraordinary
OL,9,Freally, I think Geldof, the
OL,10,Fpersonality, the intelligence, the
OL,11,Ffocus the foul-mouthedness; just an
OL,12,Fextraordinary person. It was a moment
OL,13,Fin time, wasn't it?"
OL,15,FGreatest Hits Radio is recreating the
OL,16,F1985 Live Aid broadcast in its
OL,17,Fentirety in a 10-hour special, hosted
OL,18,Fby Simon Mayo, featuring all of the
OL,19,Foriginal live performances from the
OL,20,Flikes of David Bowie, The Who and Sir
OL,21,FPaul McCartney.
